{% extends "::base.html.twig" %}

{% block body %}
    <h1>Home</h1>
    {% if is_granted("IS_AUTHENTICATED_FULLY") %}
        Welcome {{app.user.username}}
        <a href="{{path('fos_user_security_logout')}}">Logout</a>
    {% else %}
        <a href="{{path('fos_user_security_login')}}">Login</a>
    {% endif %}
    <p>
        This is the default homepage.
    </p>
    <p>
        The main goal of this template is to integrate FOSUser and FOSFacebook bundles working together and properly configured.
        Watch the documentation <a href="https://github.com/djepo/TemplateViergeSymfony2/blob/master/README.md">here</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
        Feel free to modify the CSS, all the templating shown here is only an example.
        To reset this, remove the folowing folders:
    </p>
        <ul>
            <li>src/djepo/Resources/public/css</li>
            <li>src/djepo/Resources/public/js</li>
            <li>web/bundles/djepomain/css</li>
            <li>web/bundles/djepomain/js</li>
        </ul>
    <p>
        Then, modify app/Resources/views/base.html.twig links to CSS and JS files.
        You can also remove JQuery if you want, and integrate your own Javascripts framework.
    </p>
    <p>
        For all the work, this is a Symfony 2 template !
        Check tutorials over the Web to learn how to use it, this is only a start template ;)
    </p>
{% endblock %}